00:05:15.570 --> 00:05:18.297
And we said, we're not
gong to change the product.

00:05:18.297 --> 00:05:19.880
That thing that we've
been delivering,

00:05:19.880 --> 00:05:24.190
that messy in the
bag, they want that.

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:26.790
What we're going to do is we're
going to start promising that

00:05:26.790 --> 00:05:29.770
to them, because
what was out of whack

00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:34.020
was the customer's desire was
not in line with the promise

00:05:34.020 --> 00:05:36.335
that the company was
making about their product.

00:05:36.335 --> 00:05:37.210
They had the product.

00:05:37.210 --> 00:05:38.880
They had exactly
what they wanted,

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:41.030
this big, messy, drippy thing.

00:05:41.030 --> 00:05:44.600
And so instead of
changing it, we

00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:49.420
recognized we started speaking
the language of the people who

00:05:49.420 --> 00:05:49.990
were hungry.

